2025-12-12 | Josephus Problem – Last Remaining Person

	Question
Given two integers n and k,  
return the position of the person who survives after repeatedly eliminating every kth person.

	Approach
1.	This is the classic **Josephus Problem**.
2.	Instead of simulating the entire process (which would be slow), we use a **mathematical recurrence**.
3.	Let:
		J(n, k) = position of the survivor (0-based indexing).
4.	Recurrence relation:
		J(1, k) = 0  
		J(n, k) = (J(n − 1, k) + k) % n
5.	Once we compute J(n, k) in **0-based indexing**, convert it to **1-based indexing** by adding 1.
6.	This solution runs in linear time and constant space.
7.	Time Complexity: O(n)  
   Space Complexity: O(1)

	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int josephus(int n, int k) {
        // Base case
        if (n == 1)
            return 1;

        // Recursive case (1-based indexing)
        return (josephus(n - 1, k) + k - 1) % n + 1;
    }

    int findTheWinner(int n, int k) {
        return josephus(n, k);
    }
};
